1
00:00:01,902 --> 00:00:03,668
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.

2
00:00:03,738 --> 00:00:06,137
YOU PEOPLE ONLY UNDERSTAND
ONE THING-- POWER.

3
00:00:07,407 --> 00:00:09,574
- DADDY, GET BACK!
- SHOOT HIM!

4
00:00:29,729 --> 00:00:31,897
WELCOME BACK
TO THE CENTRE, JAROD.

5
00:00:33,367 --> 00:00:36,868
SETTLE DOWN
OR I'LL BASH YOU AGAIN!

6
00:00:42,776 --> 00:00:46,211
<i> [ Sniffs, Sighs ]</i>
<i> HE STILL STINKS.</i>

7
00:00:46,279 --> 00:00:49,547
ON THE WAY TO THE SHOWER,
HE FREAKED. THOUGHT HE WAS
GONNA CHEW MY HEART OUT.

8
00:00:49,616 --> 00:00:52,117
<i> IT TOOK A LITTLE SWIPE</i>
<i> FROM THE MOTIVATOR</i>
<i> TO CALM HIM DOWN.</i>

9
00:00:52,186 --> 00:00:54,219
[ Grunts ]

10
00:00:54,287 --> 00:00:58,256
IF YOU DON'T WANT
TO GO TO THE SHOWERS,
I'LL BRING THE SHOWERS TO YOU.

11
00:00:59,793 --> 00:01:01,759
<i>[ Spits ]</i>

12
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:10,535
[ Grunting ]

13
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:22,147
ENOUGH!

14
00:01:23,383 --> 00:01:28,287
<i>WE DON'T WANT HIM DEAD,</i>
<i>JUST LESS ODIFEROUS.</i>

15
00:01:28,355 --> 00:01:31,823
CLEAN THE FILTH OFF YOURSELF,
THEN DO THE WALLS.

16
00:01:35,662 --> 00:01:38,163
- YOU CLEAN IT.
- [ Chuckling ]

17
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,734
THE WORLD IS CHANGING.

18
00:01:42,803 --> 00:01:47,071
<i>MR. PARKER IS GONE.</i>
<i> MR. RAINES IS GONE.</i>

19
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:50,742
MISS PARKER IS...
GOD ONLY KNOWS WHERE.

20
00:01:52,712 --> 00:01:54,946
BUT YOU AND I ARE HERE,

21
00:01:55,015 --> 00:01:56,948
AND I'M IN CHARGE.

22
00:02:27,915 --> 00:02:30,382
[ Crackling ]

23
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,360
[ Gasping ]

24
00:03:15,429 --> 00:03:17,362
LIKE I SAID,
THE WORLD'S CHANGING.

25
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:21,899
NO! NO! NO!
YOU BASTARDS!

26
00:03:21,968 --> 00:03:24,336
NO! NO! NO!

27
00:03:24,404 --> 00:03:27,439
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

28
00:03:27,508 --> 00:03:29,907
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

29
00:03:29,977 --> 00:03:33,177
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

30
00:03:33,247 --> 00:03:36,648
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

31
00:03:36,717 --> 00:03:40,151
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

32
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:42,420
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

33
00:03:42,489 --> 00:03:45,790
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

34
00:03:45,859 --> 00:03:48,059
- THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.
- PREFERABLY.

35
00:03:48,128 --> 00:03:50,295
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>

36
00:03:50,363 --> 00:03:52,130
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

37
00:04:02,842 --> 00:04:05,344
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

38
00:04:11,151 --> 00:04:14,018
NO! NO!
YOU BASTARDS!

39
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:19,124
<i>THAT WAS THREE WEEKS AGO.</i>
<i>SINCE THEN WE'VE BEEN WORKING</i>
<i>ON MAKING HIM MORE MANAGEABLE.</i>

40
00:04:19,193 --> 00:04:21,159
WHY HAVEN'T I BEEN ALLOWED
TO SEE HIM?

41
00:04:21,228 --> 00:04:23,662
<i> - LOOK AT HIM.</i>
<i> HE WAS OUT OF CONTROL.</i>
- WAS?

42
00:04:23,731 --> 00:04:27,833
THE WORLD IS CHANGING,
AND SO IS BOY WONDER.

43
00:04:27,901 --> 00:04:30,001
<i> [ Screaming ]</i>

44
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:33,538
LISTEN TO ME, LYLE.
YOU'RE A SICK MAN.

45
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:36,741
I'M A PERSUASIVE MAN.

46
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:42,314
<i> JAROD?</i>
<i> I HAVE A PROJECT THAT I'D</i>
<i> LIKE YOU TO DO FOR ME.</i>

47
00:04:42,383 --> 00:04:46,651
ANYTHING YOU WANT,
MR. LYLE.

48
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:49,187
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> BRAINWASHING'S NOT POSSIBLE</i>
<i> WITH JAROD.</i>

49
00:04:49,256 --> 00:04:51,623
OH, WE ALL HAVE
AN ACHILLES' HEEL.

50
00:04:51,692 --> 00:04:54,258
IN JAROD'S CASE,
IT'S FAMILY.

51
00:04:54,327 --> 00:04:56,661
<i>THE ONE HE SO DESPERATELY</i>
<i>WANTS BACK.</i>

52
00:04:56,729 --> 00:05:00,398
IF YOU WANNA HEAR
ABOUT MOMMY AND DADDY,
JUST TRUST ME.

53
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:03,268
<i> [ Jarod Crying ]</i>

54
00:05:05,505 --> 00:05:08,873
- I LOVE THAT PART.
- LYLE, PLEASE LET ME GO TO HIM.

55
00:05:08,942 --> 00:05:13,178
SYDNEY, IF IT WERE UP TO ME,
YOU TWO COULD GO ON
A FATHER-SON PICNIC,

56
00:05:13,247 --> 00:05:17,448
<i>BUT THE ISOLATION ORDERS</i>
<i>COME FROM THE TRIUMVIRATE--</i>
<i>BIG MUTUMBO.</i>

57
00:05:24,858 --> 00:05:26,891
I GOT HERE
AS QUICKLY AS I COULD.

58
00:05:29,896 --> 00:05:32,797
SYDNEY,
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME.

59
00:05:32,866 --> 00:05:35,032
WE HAVEN'T FINISHED
TALKING ABOUT JAROD!

60
00:05:35,101 --> 00:05:39,771
JAROD IS NO LONGER THE MOST
IMPORTANT THING IN THE WORLD,
AND TOMORROW HE LEAVES FOREVER.

61
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:43,875
HE'S MUTUMBO'S PROPERTY,
AND I, FOR ONE, AM NOT GONNA
CROSS THAT CRAZY ZULU.

62
00:05:43,944 --> 00:05:47,946
DID YOU SEE THE LOOK ON
HIS FACE WHEN HE TOOK RAINES
AND MY FATHER AWAY?

63
00:05:50,451 --> 00:05:53,051
JUST, UH, TAKE IN A MOVIE.

64
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,052
<i> GET A MASSAGE.</i>

65
00:05:55,121 --> 00:05:58,056
CHECK OUT THE AMPUTEE DWARVES
DOWN IN SL 6.

66
00:05:58,124 --> 00:06:00,058
JUST FORGET ABOUT JAROD.

67
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:06,898
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>YOU STOLE A D.S.A.</i>
<i>FROM LYLE?</i>

68
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:09,301
EVER SINCE MUTUMBO'S PUT THAT
THUMBLESS MANIAC IN CHARGE,

69
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:12,403
MORE BODIES HAVE BEEN
DROPPIN' AROUND HERE THAN
ST. VALENTINE'S DAY MASSACRE.

70
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:15,139
<i>DID HE TELL YOU WHERE</i>
<i>MISS PARKER'S HOSPITALIZED?</i>

71
00:06:15,209 --> 00:06:18,243
<i> NO. HE PLAYED DUMB</i>
<i> ON THAT TOO.</i>
<i>WHO'S THE ALBINO?</i>

72
00:06:18,311 --> 00:06:20,912
SOMEONE MORE IMPORTANT
THAN JAROD.

73
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:24,081
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>WHO COULD BE MORE IMPORTANT</i>
<i>THAN JAROD?</i>

74
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:27,152
I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE THE WORLD
REALLY<i> IS</i> CHANGING.

75
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:35,960
<i>[ Man Screaming ]</i>

76
00:06:39,266 --> 00:06:41,266
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>STOP THE VOICES!</i>

77
00:06:45,272 --> 00:06:48,873
NURSE, UH, I'M LOOKING
FOR MY DAUGHTER.

78
00:06:50,276 --> 00:06:52,778
AT THE END OF THE HALL.

79
00:06:52,846 --> 00:06:57,015
OH! OH, MY!
OH, MY ANGEL!

80
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:59,084
[ Grunts ]
<i> DADDY?</i>

81
00:06:59,152 --> 00:07:01,219
WHERE--

82
00:07:04,925 --> 00:07:08,359
OH! OH, THANK YOU, LORD.

83
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:12,029
MY ANGEL, I AM SO SORRY.
<i> [ Monitor Beeping ]</i>

84
00:07:12,099 --> 00:07:15,567
- IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.
- IT IS ALL MY FAULT.

85
00:07:15,635 --> 00:07:20,038
ARE YOU OKAY?
THEY KEPT ME DRUGGED
IN I.C.U. FOR THREE WEEKS.

86
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:23,108
YOU'RE THE FIRST VISITOR
I'VE SEEN.

87
00:07:23,176 --> 00:07:25,409
YEAH. I NOTICED.

88
00:07:25,478 --> 00:07:28,346
YEAH, IT'S A DAMN GOOD THING,
ANGEL, HUH?

89
00:07:28,415 --> 00:07:30,581
THOSE BASTARDS
DON'T KNOW WHERE I AM.

90
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:33,151
THEY DON'T KNOW I'M HERE,
AND WE'RE GONNA KEEP IT
THAT WAY.

91
00:07:33,219 --> 00:07:36,320
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?
EQUATORIAL AFRICA.

92
00:07:36,389 --> 00:07:39,056
THE TRIUMVIRATE MUST BE HAPPY
THEY GOT JAROD BACK.

93
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,058
OH, YEAH,
YOU'D THINK SO.

94
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,961
INSTEAD, THEY THREW ONE
RIGHT NASTY SOIREE...

95
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:46,531
FOR ME
AND THAT WHEEZING
BASTARD RAINES.

96
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:50,568
I'M BEGINNING TO WONDER
ABOUT HIS LOYALTY.
BEGINNING TO--

97
00:07:50,637 --> 00:07:55,373
THE BULLET IN MY BACK
WAS MEANT FOR YOU.

98
00:07:55,442 --> 00:07:58,242
[ Chuckling ]
CAN'T KILL A PARKER.
NEVER.

99
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:01,646
I GOT BRIGITTE OUT ALREADY.
GOTTA KEEP THAT BABY.

100
00:08:01,715 --> 00:08:03,915
GOTTA HAVE THAT BABY,
ESPECIALLY ALIVE.

101
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:06,450
DADDY, WHAT THE HELL'S
GOING ON?

102
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:10,421
SAME AS USUAL-- JAROD.
HE'S THE KEY TO OUR
SURVIVAL-- ALL OF US.

103
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:14,559
OH, CAN'T TALK.
NOT HERE. NOT NOW.
YOU'RE SCARING ME.

104
00:08:14,628 --> 00:08:17,695
OH, WE CAN'T HAVE THAT.
I MEAN, THAT'S WHAT THEY WANT.
CAN'T HAVE THAT.

105
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:19,764
CAN'T GIVE THEM THE EDGE.

106
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,400
- [ Clears Throat ]
- SHE'S NOT SUPPOSED TO
HAVE VISITORS.

107
00:08:22,469 --> 00:08:25,537
- I WAS JUST LEAVING.
- ME TOO.
I'M DISCHARGING MYSELF.

108
00:08:25,605 --> 00:08:28,440
- ONLY YOUR PSYCHIATRIST
CAN DISCHARGE YOU.
- THE PSYCHIATRIST?

109
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:30,442
I WAS SHOT!

110
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:34,278
<i>SINCE WHEN DO HEAD SHRINKERS</i>
<i>USE SCALPELS?</i>

111
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:36,514
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>I WANT MY MOMMY!</i>

112
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:39,417
OH, SHE PROBABLY WENT
TO CALL SOMEBODY.

113
00:08:39,486 --> 00:08:42,454
I HOPE I CAN TRUST YOU NOT
TO TELL ANYBODY I WAS HERE.

114
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:44,822
DADDY, DON'T LEAVE ME.

115
00:08:44,891 --> 00:08:47,425
I'LL COME BACK
WHEN I CAN EXPLAIN. HUH?

116
00:08:47,494 --> 00:08:51,496
OH, WHO WAS THAT,
UH, PLAYWRIGHT WITH
THE WHITE BEARD?

117
00:08:51,564 --> 00:08:53,998
YOUR MOTHER USED TO
READ HIM ALL THE TIME--
WITH ALL THAT PUNCTUATION.

118
00:08:54,067 --> 00:08:57,168
- SHAW?
- YEAH, WELL, WHATEVER.

119
00:08:57,237 --> 00:08:59,670
LISTEN, THERE'S A QUOTE
I WANT YOU TO REMEMBER.

120
00:08:59,739 --> 00:09:02,072
<i> "A FAMILY IS A TYRANNY...</i>

121
00:09:02,141 --> 00:09:06,143
<i> RULED OVER</i>
<i> BY ITS WEAKEST MEMBER."</i>

122
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:09,147
ITS<i> WEAKEST</i> MEMBER.
DON'T FORGET THAT.

123
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:12,449
OH, DADDY.

124
00:09:12,518 --> 00:09:16,153
<i>DADDY. DADDY.</i>

125
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:20,658
<i>♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪</i>

126
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:25,463
♪ GEESE WALK BAREFOOT ♪♪

127
00:09:25,532 --> 00:09:29,867
SO WHAT'S IN STORE TONIGHT?
ANOTHER DATE WITH MR. LYLE'S
JUMPER CABLE?

128
00:09:29,936 --> 00:09:32,103
<i> DIFFERENT GAME</i>
<i> THIS TIME, JAROD.</i>

129
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:35,006
ARE WE TAKING ANOTHER TRIP?
<i> THIS TIME IT'S NOT</i>
<i> SO DEPENDABLE.</i>

130
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:38,843
VACCINES. HEPATITIS "A,"
MALARIA, TYPHOID.

131
00:09:40,546 --> 00:09:43,481
- AFRICA.
- YOU ARE AS SMART
AS THEY SAY.

132
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:46,117
- LOT OF GOOD
IT'S DONE ME LATELY.
- ARM.

133
00:09:48,555 --> 00:09:50,488
[ Grunts ]

134
00:09:50,556 --> 00:09:53,324
♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪

135
00:09:53,393 --> 00:09:55,894
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> TELL ME WHERE JAROD IS,</i>
<i> ANGELO.</i>

136
00:09:55,962 --> 00:09:57,962
<i>FIND HIM FOR ME.</i>

137
00:10:08,574 --> 00:10:11,009
HEY. WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

138
00:10:11,078 --> 00:10:15,880
I'M USING ANGELO'S EMPATHETIC
ABILITIES TO TRY AND DETERMINE
WHERE JAROD IS BEING KEPT.

139
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:19,350
<i> HOW DOES THE, UH, FREAK</i>
<i> WITH THE FLOWBEE FIT IN?</i>

140
00:10:19,419 --> 00:10:22,386
<i>IN CASE OF SUSPICIONS,</i>
<i>I WANTED THE LAB TO BE</i>
<i>BUSINESS AS USUAL.</i>

141
00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:24,455
AH. USUAL.

142
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:29,226
SYDNEY. SCARED.
YES, ANGELO.

143
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:32,296
SYDNEY IS SCARED THAT HE'LL
NEVER SEE JAROD AGAIN.

144
00:10:32,365 --> 00:10:36,033
<i>EMPATH JAROD.</i>
<i>TELL ME WHERE</i>
<i>THEY'RE HOLDING HIM.</i>

145
00:10:36,102 --> 00:10:38,703
<i> - [ Broots ] ANY LUCK?</i>
- NOT YET. YOU?

146
00:10:38,772 --> 00:10:41,339
I FOUND SOME BREAD CRUMBS
THAT MAY LEAD US TO MISS PARKER.

147
00:10:41,408 --> 00:10:45,209
<i>A SHORT CALL COMES IN AT THE</i>
<i>EXACT SAME TIME FROM A HOSPITAL</i>
<i>50 MILES WEST OF HERE.</i>

148
00:10:45,278 --> 00:10:47,044
PATIENT UPDATE.
<i> EXACTLY.</i>

149
00:10:47,113 --> 00:10:51,883
BEFORE I COULD TRACK WHERE
THE CALLS WENT TO, LYLE'S ALBINO
CAME BLUSTERING IN.

150
00:10:51,952 --> 00:10:53,952
<i> SOMETHING ABOUT</i>
<i> A PRIORITY COMMUNICATION.</i>

151
00:10:54,020 --> 00:10:56,220
SOMETHING CALLED
SI-- SILENCE.

152
00:10:56,289 --> 00:10:58,223
SILENCE, HUH?

153
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:08,065
<i>[ Angelo ]</i>
<i>ANGELO HAPPY. FIND JAROD.</i>

154
00:11:08,134 --> 00:11:12,303
IF YOU WANNA HEAR
ABOUT MOMMY AND DADDY,
JUST TRUST ME.

155
00:11:28,888 --> 00:11:31,222
[ Whispering ]
JAROD. JAROD.

156
00:11:31,290 --> 00:11:33,290
SYDNEY.
ARE YOU OKAY?

157
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:36,494
IS IT TRUE?

158
00:11:36,562 --> 00:11:40,565
IS IT TRUE THAT THEY CAPTURED
MY FATHER AND THE BOY?
DID LYLE TELL YOU THAT?

159
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:45,236
HE SAID ONLY ONE OF THEM
SURVIVED, AND I'D FIND OUT
WHICH ONE IN AFRICA,

160
00:11:45,304 --> 00:11:47,304
IF I COOPERATE.

161
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:50,074
YOU TRUST LYLE?
DON'T YOU?

162
00:11:50,143 --> 00:11:51,976
<i> [ Door Opens ]</i>

163
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:54,678
<i> WELL, DON'T YOU, SYDNEY?</i>

164
00:11:54,747 --> 00:11:57,915
<i> I SEE EVEN YOU</i>
<i> FOUND THIS NEEDLE</i>
<i> IN OUR LITTLE HAYSTACK.</i>

165
00:11:57,984 --> 00:11:59,984
I WONDER HOW.

166
00:12:01,188 --> 00:12:03,788
I NEVER LIKED YOU.

167
00:12:03,857 --> 00:12:06,991
I'M NOT EVEN SURE
WHAT THE HELL YOU ARE.

168
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:09,293
<i> COME ON, JAROD.</i>
<i> TIME TO GO.</i>

169
00:12:12,866 --> 00:12:15,700
NO INJECTIONS
THIS TIME, JAROD.

170
00:12:15,768 --> 00:12:18,369
-<i> [ Pills Rattling ]</i>
- SEDATIVES.

171
00:12:18,438 --> 00:12:20,605
- JAROD.
- IT'S OKAY, SYDNEY.

172
00:12:21,975 --> 00:12:25,343
- I PREFER TO SLEEP
THROUGH THIS.
- JAROD, DON'T!

173
00:12:27,947 --> 00:12:29,881
LYLE, I WON'T ALLOW THIS!

174
00:12:29,949 --> 00:12:32,350
DENY IT AS SWEET SORROW
IF YOU WANT, SYDNEY,

175
00:12:32,419 --> 00:12:35,052
BUT YOU TWO ARE PARTING,
SO BE A MAN.

176
00:12:35,121 --> 00:12:37,122
SAY ADIOS.

177
00:12:41,595 --> 00:12:43,527
GOOD-BYE, SYDNEY.

178
00:12:48,235 --> 00:12:51,702
TONGUE?
THAT-A-BOY.

179
00:12:54,007 --> 00:12:57,141
UH, SYDNEY?
PUT HIM AWAY.

180
00:13:01,815 --> 00:13:04,549
<i>JAROD'S SOUL IS CLOUDED.</i>

181
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:12,390
HIS MIND IS STILL SHARP.

182
00:13:17,596 --> 00:13:19,864
<i> GOOD NIGHT, SWEET PRINCE.</i>

183
00:13:19,933 --> 00:13:22,333
WE'RE GOOD TO GO.

184
00:13:22,402 --> 00:13:25,737
<i>THE TOWER CALLED.</i>
<i>WE HAVE A PRIORITY PASSENGER</i>
<i>TO BE DROPPED OFF.</i>

185
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:27,838
LEVEL "A" PROJECT
CALLED SILENCE.

186
00:13:27,907 --> 00:13:31,842
UNTIL WE CROSS THE ATLANTIC,
WE'RE NOT STOPPIN'
ANYWHERE FOR ANYONE.

187
00:13:31,911 --> 00:13:33,844
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>MR. LYLE SAYS WE ARE.</i>

188
00:13:33,913 --> 00:13:38,215
I'LL TELL YOU WHERE WE'RE GOING
WHEN WE GET IN THE AIR.

189
00:13:59,806 --> 00:14:03,908
<i>YES, MR. LYLE.</i>
<i>I HAVE THE BLUEPRINTS</i>
<i>AND EVERYTHING I NEED.</i>

190
00:14:03,977 --> 00:14:08,046
<i> TELL OUR CLIENTS AT RAYLOR</i>
<i> THAT AS SOON AS OUR INSIDE</i>
<i> PERSON GETS THE E.T.A.,</i>

191
00:14:08,114 --> 00:14:11,115
SILENCE WILL GO DOWN
FLAWLESSLY THIS TIME.

192
00:14:11,184 --> 00:14:15,786
<i> WELL, THE C-4 WILL CATALYZE</i>
<i> THE ON-SITE ACCELERANT</i>
<i> AND BURN WHITE HOT.</i>

193
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:18,789
<i>EVEN IF SOMEONE COULD DIG</i>
<i>THROUGH THE DEBRIS,</i>

194
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:21,593
<i> OUR CORPORATE CUSTOMERS</i>
<i> CAN REST ASSURED...</i>

195
00:14:21,661 --> 00:14:25,262
THERE'LL BE NO TRACE
OF EVEN THE TIMING DEVICE
THAT SURVIVES.

196
00:14:25,331 --> 00:14:28,933
OH, I GUARANTEE YOU--
THERE'LL BE NO TRACE LEFT
OF THE NASH FAMILY...

197
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:37,208
<i>ANY RESIDUAL FALLOUT WILL</i>
<i>JUST HELP TO MASK THE I.D.'s</i>
<i>OF OUR INTENDED TARGETS.</i>

198
00:14:39,011 --> 00:14:40,911
I'LL CONTACT YOU
WHEN I'M IN PLACE.

199
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:51,622
HAVEN'T YOU PEOPLE
DESTROYED ENOUGH LIVES?
WHAT THE HELL'S GOIN' ON?

200
00:14:51,691 --> 00:14:54,959
<i> IF A BULLET</i>
<i> PENETRATES THE JET'S SKIN,</i>
<i> IT CAN EXPLODE.</i>

201
00:14:57,997 --> 00:15:00,264
NOT IF SOMETHING
PLUGS THE HOLE.

202
00:15:09,375 --> 00:15:11,375
<i>[ Alarm Beeping ]</i>

203
00:15:15,047 --> 00:15:17,081
COME ON! COME ON!

204
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:39,369
- [ Gasps ]
- GOOD MORNING, SWEET PRINCE.

205
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:42,840
<i>FORTUNATELY,</i>
<i>I WAS ABLE TO LAND THE PLANE</i>
<i>IN ALMOST ONE PIECE.</i>

206
00:15:42,909 --> 00:15:44,809
MY LUCKY DAY.

207
00:15:47,246 --> 00:15:49,012
WHERE'S MR. WHITE?

208
00:15:49,081 --> 00:15:53,584
HE DISAPPEARED.
ANY IDEA WHERE HE MIGHT
HAVE DISAPPEARED TO?

209
00:15:53,653 --> 00:15:55,586
EVEN IF I KNEW,
I WOULDN'T TELL YOU.

210
00:16:05,098 --> 00:16:08,599
<i>[ Lyle ] YES, MUTUMBO,</i>
<i>I UNDERSTAND CLEARLY EVERY WORD</i>
<i>THAT YOU ARE SAYING,</i>

211
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:12,003
AND I ASSURE YOU THAT
THE IRONY OF JAROD'S ESCAPE
IS NOT LOST ON ME EITHER.

212
00:16:12,071 --> 00:16:13,905
<i>[ Mutumbo On Phone ]</i>
<i>SIR, ARE YOU BEING FACETIOUS?</i>

213
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:17,241
FACETIOUS? NO. NO.
OF COURSE I'M NOT BEING
FACETIOUS, SIR.

214
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:19,576
<i>[ Mutumbo ]</i>
<i>YOU UNDERSTAND?</i>

215
00:16:19,646 --> 00:16:22,779
<i>YES, I UNDERSTAND THE</i>
<i>IMPORTANCE OF REACQUIRING JAROD</i>
<i>AS IT RELATES TO SILENCE, SIR,</i>

216
00:16:22,848 --> 00:16:25,883
<i>BUT, AS YOU KNOW,</i>
<i>WE HAVE AN INSIDE PERSON.</i>

217
00:16:25,951 --> 00:16:30,354
SO, OUR FRIENDS AT RAYLOR CAN
REST ASSURED THAT THE PROJECT
WILL NOT BE COMPROMISED.

218
00:16:30,422 --> 00:16:33,690
- [ Mutumbo ] IT BETTER NOT BE.
<i>- YES, SIR. YOU HAVE MY WORD.</i>

219
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:37,962
ALL RIGHT.
IT SEEMS LIKE THE WORLD
HASN'T CHANGED SO MUCH.

220
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:39,963
OKAY, SYDNEY,
YOU WERE RIGHT,
AND I WAS WRONG.

221
00:16:40,032 --> 00:16:42,900
BUT I WOULD RATHER
BE ALIVE AND WRONG
THAN DEAD RIGHT.

222
00:16:42,968 --> 00:16:45,235
AND IF WE DON'T
GET JAROD BACK,

223
00:16:45,304 --> 00:16:48,071
I'M NOT THE ONLY ONE MUTUMBO'S
GONNA PERSONALLY REEDUCATE.

224
00:16:50,276 --> 00:16:53,243
- OH. OH, SORRY
FOR BURSTING IN.
- WHAT?

225
00:16:53,312 --> 00:16:56,547
YOU WON'T BELIEVE
WHO I JUST SAW WALKIN' AROUND
THE HALLWAYS ALIVE AS DAY.

226
00:16:56,616 --> 00:17:01,184
I MEAN, RUMOR HAS IT
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE DEAD,
BUT HE'S, UH, NOT.

227
00:17:02,889 --> 00:17:04,889
[ Wheezing ]

228
00:17:04,957 --> 00:17:07,157
GLAD TO DISAPPOINT YOU.

229
00:17:07,226 --> 00:17:10,294
HUH.
[ Gasps ]

230
00:17:10,363 --> 00:17:14,231
IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK
IN THE BOSOM OF THE CENTRE.

231
00:17:14,299 --> 00:17:16,633
<i> GOD BLESS YOU ALL!</i>

232
00:17:18,404 --> 00:17:20,438
NOW, LET'S GO CATCH JAROD.

233
00:17:20,506 --> 00:17:22,439
AMEN.

234
00:17:34,753 --> 00:17:39,322
<i>A PH.D. IN NUCLEAR PHYSICS</i>
<i>FROM M.I.T. AND A DOCTORATE IN</i>
<i>RADIOISOTOPIC DESIGN FROM USC.</i>

235
00:17:39,391 --> 00:17:41,391
THAT'S A PRETTY
IMPRESSIVE SHEEPSKIN.

236
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:45,128
YOU SEE WHAT THEY LOOK LIKE
ON THE INTERNET, PRESS PRINT,
AND YOU'RE SOMEBODY ELSE.

237
00:17:45,197 --> 00:17:47,565
OH, UH, JEANIE,
THIS IS DR. JAROD HICKUM.

238
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:50,333
HELPED DESIGN
THE PROPULSION SYSTEM ON
THE CASSINI PROBE FOR NASA.

239
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:52,903
NICE TO MEET YOU.
WEREN'T THOSE
RUSSIAN-MADE REACTORS?

240
00:17:52,972 --> 00:17:55,105
I BELIEVE
THAT YOU'RE THINKING
OF THE TOPAZ II.

241
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:59,977
THE CASSINI'S REACTORS WERE
CHANDON DESIGNED, WITH 72 POUNDS
OF 238 AT THE CORE.

242
00:18:00,046 --> 00:18:03,047
WELL, I HOPE
YOUR EXPERTISE CAN HELP US
WITH THE NEPTUNE PROBE.

243
00:18:03,115 --> 00:18:05,115
WE'RE, UM, THREE MONTHS
BEHIND SCHEDULE.

244
00:18:05,184 --> 00:18:07,817
AND WE'VE LOST OUR TWO
BEST RESEARCHERS.

245
00:18:07,886 --> 00:18:10,353
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>WELL, I'M HERE</i>
<i>TO DO EVERYTHING I CAN.</i>

246
00:18:12,858 --> 00:18:15,125
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>

247
00:18:15,194 --> 00:18:18,195
<i> SYDNEY.</i>

248
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:20,897
MISS PARKER.

249
00:18:20,966 --> 00:18:24,201
MISS PARKER,
WE'VE BEEN SEARCHING
EVERYWHERE FOR YOU.

250
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,470
THANK GOD YOU'RE--
ALIVE? HARDLY.

251
00:18:26,539 --> 00:18:30,407
<i>AND THESE MORONS IN HERE</i>
<i>WON'T LET ME OUT.</i>

252
00:18:30,476 --> 00:18:34,011
OH, I GET MY STRENGTH BACK,
I SWEAR I'M GOING POSTAL.

253
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,012
THAT'S WHAT
THEY'RE AFRAID OF.

254
00:18:36,082 --> 00:18:39,082
ACCORDING TO THIS CHART,
YOU WERE ADMITTED UNDER
A SUICIDE WATCH.

255
00:18:39,151 --> 00:18:42,052
SUICIDE?
I WAS SHOT IN THE BACK!

256
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:45,055
- ONLY YOUR NEXT OF KIN
CAN OKAY YOUR DISCHARGE.
- NEXT OF KIN.

257
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,491
<i> PARKER, HAVE YOU HEARD</i>
<i> FROM YOUR FATHER?</i>

258
00:18:50,729 --> 00:18:54,764
- NO.
- WELL, SOMEBODY SURE WANTS
TO KEEP YOU IN HERE.

259
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:58,935
- YEAH, THE WHEEZING
SACK OF BONES RAINES.
- I'M NOT CERTAIN THAT'S RIGHT.

260
00:18:59,004 --> 00:19:01,605
<i>RAINES MAY HAVE SPENT</i>
<i>SOME TIME ON MUTUMBO'S</i>
<i>SIDE OF THE STREET,</i>

261
00:19:01,674 --> 00:19:04,208
BUT HE'S ACTING
MORE LIKE HE'S BEEN IN
MISTER ROGERS' NEIGHBORHOOD.

262
00:19:04,276 --> 00:19:07,210
HE FOUND RELIGION--
OR IT WAS GIVEN TO HIM.
I DON'T BUY IT.

263
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,946
THERE'S SOMETHIN'
GOIN' DOWN AT THE CENTRE,
AND THEY DON'T WANT ME AROUND.

264
00:19:10,015 --> 00:19:13,884
LYLE KEEPS SAYING, "THE WORLD
IS CHANGING." BESIDES RAINES'S
REBIRTH, JAROD HAS ESCAPED.

265
00:19:13,952 --> 00:19:18,088
<i>LYLE HAS SOME ALBINO</i>
<i>RUNNING A PRIORITY PROJECT</i>
<i>CALLED SILENCE.</i>

266
00:19:18,156 --> 00:19:20,457
I GOTTA GET OUTTA HERE.
[ Groans ]

267
00:19:20,526 --> 00:19:23,693
YOU STILL NEED REST.
AT LEAST ANOTHER 24 HOURS.

268
00:19:23,762 --> 00:19:27,931
TWENTY-FOUR HOURS,
AND THEN I'M BLOWIN'
THIS CAT SCAN STAND.

269
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,902
I WANT YOU TO FIND OUT
EVERYTHING YOU CAN ABOUT
THE ALBINO AND SILENCE.

270
00:19:31,971 --> 00:19:34,938
THEY MAY HAVE ME DOWN,
BUT I'LL BE DAMNED
IF I'M OUT. GO!

271
00:19:38,811 --> 00:19:40,978
[ Chattering ]

272
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:11,842
-<i> JAROD.</i>
<i>  WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?</i>
- JEANIE. HI.

273
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:15,246
I WAS TRYING TO GET A LEG UP
ON THINGS AND I THOUGHT I WOULD
GO STRAIGHT TO THE SOURCE.

274
00:20:15,314 --> 00:20:18,115
WHAT PART OF THE PROJECT
WERE THE NASHES WORKING ON?

275
00:20:18,184 --> 00:20:20,784
THEY WERE HEADING UP
THE RESEARCH FOR RAYLOR
CORPORATION'S PROPULSION SYSTEM.

276
00:20:20,853 --> 00:20:24,688
<i>THEY MADE</i>
<i>SOME INCREDIBLE DISCOVERIES</i>
<i>WITH MULTIPLE APPLICATIONS.</i>

277
00:20:24,756 --> 00:20:27,257
BUT MOST OF THEIR WORK
WAS SEALED AFTER THE ACCIDENT.

278
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:31,094
- ACCIDENT?
- YEAH, A FREAK THING.

279
00:20:31,164 --> 00:20:35,199
THEIR SAILBOAT BLEW UP
WHILE IN PORT IN THE CARIBBEAN.
A GAS LEAK OR SOMETHING.

280
00:20:35,268 --> 00:20:37,600
- I CAN'T BELIEVE THEY'RE DEAD.
- MAYBE THEY'RE NOT.

281
00:20:41,874 --> 00:20:43,640
WHO SEALED THE DATA?

282
00:20:43,709 --> 00:20:47,211
THE WORD WAS IT ALL WENT
TO THE DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY
OFFICE IN ALBANY.

283
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:55,119
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>
<i>THIS IS SYDNEY.</i>

284
00:20:55,187 --> 00:20:59,590
<i> I HEAR SILENCE IS GOLDEN,</i>
<i> ESPECIALLY AT THE CENTRE.</i>

285
00:20:59,659 --> 00:21:03,994
THERE IS A PROJECT
CALLED SILENCE, BUT GOD
ONLY KNOWS WHAT IT IS.

286
00:21:04,063 --> 00:21:06,496
- IS THAT MR. BROOTS I HEAR?
- YEAH. HOW'D YOU KNOW?

287
00:21:06,565 --> 00:21:09,400
DEVIATED SEPTUM.
RIGHT NOSTRIL.

288
00:21:09,468 --> 00:21:12,670
WELL, I DID GET BEANED
WITH AN ETCH A SKETCH
WHEN I WAS SEVEN--

289
00:21:12,738 --> 00:21:15,038
WHAT CAN YOU TELL ME
ABOUT SILENCE?

290
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:18,509
JUST THAT LYLE AND
SOME WEIRD-LOOKING ALBINO GUY
WERE TALKIN' ABOUT IT.

291
00:21:18,577 --> 00:21:20,577
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>AH, YES. THE WHITE-HAIRED MAN.</i>

292
00:21:20,646 --> 00:21:23,480
<i>HE AND I SHARED</i>
<i>SOME FREQUENT-FLYER MILES.</i>

293
00:21:23,548 --> 00:21:27,517
I CAN'T TALK TO YOU ABOUT THIS.
WE'RE-- WE'RE SUPPOSED TO
BE TRYIN' TO CATCH YOU.

294
00:21:27,586 --> 00:21:29,919
I KNOW WHERE YOU LIVE,
MR. BROOTS.

295
00:21:29,988 --> 00:21:32,323
<i> EVEN IF WE DID</i>
<i> FIND SOMETHING OUT</i>
<i> ABOUT SILENCE--</i>

296
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:34,491
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON AROUND HERE.

297
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:37,494
I MEAN,
THEY TURNED MR. RAINES
INTO PAT ROBERTSON.

298
00:21:37,563 --> 00:21:41,164
<i>SILENCE IS ABOUT</i>
<i>THE CENTRE KILLING A MAN,</i>
<i>WOMAN AND THEIR CHILD.</i>

299
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:44,100
<i>NOW, LYLE AND THE ALBINO</i>
<i>HAVE AN INSIDE PERSON</i>
<i>HELPING THEM.</i>

300
00:21:44,170 --> 00:21:46,770
<i>MY GUESS IS SOMEONE WITHIN</i>
<i>THE DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY.</i>

301
00:21:46,839 --> 00:21:49,773
- I NEED HELP FINDING OUT WHO.
- WE'LL DO OUR BEST.

302
00:21:49,841 --> 00:21:52,609
WELL, YOU'D BETTER,
BECAUSE IF YOU DON'T,

303
00:21:52,678 --> 00:21:54,678
AN INNOCENT FAMILY
IS GOING TO DIE.

304
00:21:56,348 --> 00:21:58,281
[ Beeps ]

305
00:22:02,621 --> 00:22:04,554
<i>[ Siren Blaring ]</i>

306
00:22:04,623 --> 00:22:07,657
<i> SO, WHO'S THIS NEW HOTSHOT</i>
<i> JOINING THE NASH DETAIL,</i>
<i> INSPECTOR?</i>

307
00:22:07,726 --> 00:22:11,228
HIS NAME IS JAROD WATTS,
BUT HE IS HARDLY A HOTSHOT.

308
00:22:11,297 --> 00:22:14,364
BOTTOM THIRD IN COLLEGE,
BARELY SQUEAK-BY I.Q.

309
00:22:14,433 --> 00:22:17,401
<i> THIS GUY HAS BEEN BOUNCED</i>
<i> AROUND FROM ONE MEDIOCRE</i>
<i> ASSIGNMENT TO THE NEXT.</i>

310
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:21,371
- BUT HE HAS ONE THING ON HIS
RÉSUMÉ THAT NONE OF US HAVE.
<i>- [ Woman ] WHAT'S THAT?</i>

311
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:23,707
- THE SAME LAST NAME
AS THE UNDERSECRETARY.
- SON?

312
00:22:23,776 --> 00:22:26,243
- NEPHEW.
- OH.

313
00:22:26,312 --> 00:22:28,646
I'M SORRY I'M, UH, LATE.

314
00:22:29,715 --> 00:22:31,916
SO--

315
00:22:31,984 --> 00:22:35,752
SORRY.
UH, JAROD WATTS.

316
00:22:35,821 --> 00:22:39,255
<i>THE REASON I'M LATE IS</i>
<i>I WAS DOING A LITTLE BONING UP</i>
<i>ON THAT NASH THING.</i>

317
00:22:39,325 --> 00:22:44,327
<i> THE "NASH THING"</i>
<i> IS A P-1 WITNESS PROTECTION</i>
<i> TRANSFER, WATTS.</i>

318
00:22:44,396 --> 00:22:48,264
- PLEASE DON'T FORGET THAT.
- UH, YES, SIR.

319
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,466
<i> NOW THEN--</i>
[ Loud Clattering ]

320
00:22:52,238 --> 00:22:56,407
AGENT TIMSON WILL CONTINUE
TO BE POINT ON THE CLARE NASH
PROTECTION TEAM...

321
00:22:56,475 --> 00:22:59,743
UP UNTIL SHE IS REUNITED
WITH HUSBAND AND DAUGHTER.

322
00:22:59,811 --> 00:23:02,813
I'LL BE MAINTAINING
A CODE 3 SECURITY STATUS
ON THE NASH WOMAN.

323
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:05,683
<i> EXCUSE ME.</i>
<i> UH, ISN'T A CODE 3</i>
<i> A LITTLE BIT THIN?</i>

324
00:23:05,751 --> 00:23:08,018
<i> THAT'S THE IDEA, WATTS.</i>

325
00:23:08,086 --> 00:23:12,356
YOU SEE, A CODE 3
PROVIDES PROTECTION WITHOUT
DRAWING UNDUE ATTENTION...

326
00:23:12,424 --> 00:23:15,492
<i> TO THE LOCATION</i>
<i> SAID WITNESS</i>
<i> IS BEING HELD.</i>

327
00:23:15,561 --> 00:23:18,929
- IT'S REALLY QUITE EFFECTIVE.
- YES, SIR. CODE 3.

328
00:23:18,997 --> 00:23:21,365
[ Chuckling ]
AGENT CARLSON.

329
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:25,502
<i>PLEASE, TRY TO BRING WATTS UP</i>
<i>TO SPEED ON THE "NASH THING."</i>

330
00:23:25,570 --> 00:23:27,671
<i> I'LL TOLERATE</i>
<i> NO MISTAKES.</i>

331
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:30,040
THAT'S LUNCH.

332
00:23:45,023 --> 00:23:48,192
ANGEL, IT'S DADDY.
I LOOKED FOR YOU AT THE
HOSPITAL, BUT YOU'RE GONE.

333
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:51,361
YOU CAN'T KEEP A PARKER
UNDER WRAPS. NO, SIRREE.

334
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,897
<i>UH, WHAT I NEED TO TELL YOU</i>
<i>HAS TO BE SAID FACE-TO-FACE.</i>

335
00:23:53,966 --> 00:23:56,633
<i>I'LL BE AT YOUR PLACE</i>
<i>TONIGHT AT 9:00.</i>

336
00:23:56,702 --> 00:23:59,402
<i>NOW, YOU BE ALONE.</i>
<i>ERASE THIS TAPE.</i>

337
00:23:59,472 --> 00:24:01,939
<i>I WOULDN'T WANT</i>
<i>THE WRONG PEOPLE SHOWIN' UP.</i>

338
00:24:02,007 --> 00:24:05,409
WRONG PEOPLE. RAINES.

339
00:24:09,048 --> 00:24:12,049
<i>[ Carlson ]</i>
<i>THE NASHES' NUCLEAR RESEARCH</i>
<i>FOR THE RAYLOR CORPORATION...</i>

340
00:24:12,117 --> 00:24:14,451
WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
STRICTLY FOR SPACE
PROPULSION APPLICATIONS.

341
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:17,921
BUT WHEN THEY SUSPECTED RAYLOR
WAS SELLIN' THEIR WORK
FOR WEAPONS APPLICATIONS,

342
00:24:17,989 --> 00:24:20,323
THEY DECIDED TO BLOW
THE WHISTLE TO THE D.O.E.

343
00:24:20,392 --> 00:24:23,226
THAT'S WHEN SOMEONE TRIED
TO KILL THEM ON THE BOAT.
ARE THERE ANY LEADS?

344
00:24:23,295 --> 00:24:25,295
NONE. COMPLETELY
PROFESSIONAL JOB.

345
00:24:25,364 --> 00:24:27,697
IT TURNED OUT TO BE ALMOST
AS GOOD AS KILLING THEM.
HOW'S THAT?

346
00:24:27,766 --> 00:24:31,801
WELL, THE NASHES
GOT SEPARATED IN THE MAYHEM,
AND IT DROVE THEM UNDERGROUND.

347
00:24:31,870 --> 00:24:34,871
UNTIL THE D.O.E. FOUND
JASON NASH AND HIS DAUGHTER
LIVING IN THE CARIBBEAN.

348
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:36,940
<i> THEY WERE PLACED</i>
<i> IN PROTECTIVE CUSTODY.</i>

349
00:24:37,009 --> 00:24:41,712
JASON NASH SAID HE'D TESTIFY
IF HIS WIFE WAS FOUND AND THEY
WERE REUNITED AS A FAMILY.

350
00:24:41,781 --> 00:24:44,414
<i> WE JUST RECENTLY</i>
<i> FOUND CLARE.</i>

351
00:24:44,483 --> 00:24:47,083
TOMORROW AT 3:00
WE BRING THEM ALL BACK TOGETHER
AT THE ATOMIC RESEARCH LAB.

352
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:49,686
FAMILY REUNITED,
FAMILY TALKS.

353
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:58,862
FAMILY TALKS,
FAMILY DIES.

354
00:25:02,434 --> 00:25:06,603
<i> MY WORK HERE IS MY LIFE.</i>
<i> I'VE SPENT YEARS HERE DOING</i>
<i> THE WORK OF THE LORD.</i>

355
00:25:06,672 --> 00:25:10,874
<i>RAINES, IT'S TIME FOR YOU</i>
<i>TO PAY FOR KILLING MY MOTHER.</i>

356
00:25:10,942 --> 00:25:12,976
SAY YOUR PRAYERS,
YOU SON OF A BITCH.

357
00:25:13,045 --> 00:25:16,914
MISS PARKER,
I'D LIKE TO INTRODUCE
FATHER CONNELLEY.

358
00:25:16,982 --> 00:25:19,950
-<i> HE WAS A FRIEND</i>
<i> OF YOUR MOTHER'S.</i>
- HOW DO YOU DO?

359
00:25:22,087 --> 00:25:26,757
I LOOK FORWARD TO YOU
CONTINUING WITH YOUR
GOOD WORK, MR. RAINES.

360
00:25:27,726 --> 00:25:30,994
<i> WHAT'S YOUR GOOD WORK?</i>

361
00:25:31,063 --> 00:25:35,064
FREE EXORCISMS
FOR THE WHACK JOBS
IN RENEWAL?

362
00:25:38,337 --> 00:25:40,837
DO YOU BELIEVE IN MIRACLES,
MISS PARKER?

363
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:47,377
I BELIEVE
IN REVENGE.

364
00:25:47,446 --> 00:25:52,315
NOW TELL ME, WHY DID YOU
TRY AND KILL DADDY?

365
00:25:54,819 --> 00:25:57,587
A SELFISH, MISGUIDED ACT.

366
00:25:58,824 --> 00:26:02,792
BUT IT CAME FROM ABOVE,
AS GOD IS MY WITNESS.

367
00:26:05,497 --> 00:26:08,198
THIS KINDNESS CRAP
MAY SLAY 'EM
AT THE PARISH POTLUCK,

368
00:26:08,267 --> 00:26:11,034
BUT IT AIN'T CUTTIN' IT
WITH ME.

369
00:26:11,103 --> 00:26:13,270
THEN I'LL TURN
THE OTHER CHEEK.

370
00:26:18,610 --> 00:26:22,345
MISS PARKER,
THOSE MIRACLES I MENTIONED--

371
00:26:23,348 --> 00:26:27,818
THEY BEGIN WITH... LOVE.

372
00:26:32,458 --> 00:26:35,658
WHEN I FIND OUT
WHAT YOU'RE UP TO,

373
00:26:35,727 --> 00:26:39,963
IT'S GONNA TAKE A HELL
OF A LOT MORE THAN A PRAYER
TO SAVE YOUR SORRY ASS.

374
00:26:42,935 --> 00:26:46,236
<i> THANK YOU,</i>
<i> BUT I'M NOT HUNGRY.</i>

375
00:26:48,139 --> 00:26:50,406
MRS. NASH WON'T EAT?

376
00:26:50,475 --> 00:26:54,278
-<i> SHE'S A LITTLE FREAKED OUT.</i>
- LET ME TRY.

377
00:26:55,914 --> 00:27:00,483
I KNOW IT'S NOT GOURMET,
BUT YOU REALLY SHOULD EAT.

378
00:27:00,552 --> 00:27:02,853
IT WILL HELP YOU
KEEP YOUR STRENGTH UP.
NO.

379
00:27:07,692 --> 00:27:09,859
WHEN I WAS A KID,

380
00:27:09,929 --> 00:27:14,230
IN THE PLACE I GREW UP IN,
I NEVER WANTED TO EAT EITHER.

381
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:16,500
WHY WAS THAT,
AGENT WATTS?

382
00:27:16,568 --> 00:27:20,571
BECAUSE IT WASN'T MY BODY
THAT NEEDED NOURISHING.

383
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:23,306
IT WAS MY HEART.

384
00:27:23,375 --> 00:27:27,744
THERE WASN'T
A MEAL SATISFYING ENOUGH
OR A ROOM SAFE ENOUGH...

385
00:27:27,813 --> 00:27:32,182
TO HELP ME STOP MISSING
THE FAMILY THAT I WANTED
TO BE WITH SO BADLY.

386
00:27:32,250 --> 00:27:34,250
WELL, WHERE'S
YOUR FAMILY NOW?

387
00:27:34,319 --> 00:27:36,720
I DON'T KNOW.

388
00:27:36,789 --> 00:27:41,091
<i>IT'S THE NOT KNOWING,</i>
<i>THE WAITING, THAT'S</i>
<i>THE HARDEST PART.</i>

389
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:44,895
<i>BUT WHILE YOU WAIT,</i>
<i>MAYBE THIS CAN HELP.</i>

390
00:27:48,601 --> 00:27:52,769
C-COURTNEY GAVE ME THIS
FOR MOTHER'S DAY.

391
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:54,938
I THOUGHT I LOST IT FOREVER.

392
00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:57,874
TOMORROW
YOU'LL BE BACK TOGETHER
WITH THE REAL THING.

393
00:27:57,942 --> 00:28:00,744
I PROMISE YOU.

394
00:28:09,288 --> 00:28:12,622
I MISS THE DAYS
WHEN THE PEOPLE
I COULDN'T TRUST...

395
00:28:14,493 --> 00:28:16,893
WERE THE PEOPLE
I COULDN'T TRUST.

396
00:28:16,962 --> 00:28:19,830
YOU'VE OBVIOUSLY MET
THE NEW MR. RAINES,
MISS PARKER.

397
00:28:19,898 --> 00:28:22,899
NOW MEET MR. WHITE.
HE REPORTS TO LYLE.

398
00:28:22,968 --> 00:28:25,636
<i> SINCE WHEN DOES ANYBODY</i>
<i> REPORT TO MY BROTHER?</i>

399
00:28:25,704 --> 00:28:28,739
SINCE THE TRIUMVIRATE
GAVE HIM HIS OWN COVERT TEAM
A FEW YEARS AGO.

400
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:31,408
HIS LATEST PROJECT
IS CALLED SILENCE.

401
00:28:31,477 --> 00:28:34,311
IT'S A CORPORATE-SPONSORED
CENTRE HIT ON A COUPLE
RESEARCH SCIENTISTS.

402
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:38,181
JAROD WAS ON THAT PLANE
WITH WHITE WHEN IT WENT DOWN.

403
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:42,786
HE KNOWS THOSE INNOCENT PEOPLE
WILL DIE IF HE DOESN'T STOP HIM.
YOU KNOW HE'LL TRY.

404
00:28:42,854 --> 00:28:45,622
- IF JAROD'S GOING,
THEN SO AM I.
- HMM.

405
00:28:45,691 --> 00:28:50,026
<i>MISS PARKER'S</i>
<i>GONNA WANT TO OFF HERSELF</i>
<i>WHEN SHE HEARS THIS ONE.</i>

406
00:28:50,095 --> 00:28:52,328
CAN ANYBODY
SPARE A NOOSE?
MISS PARKER!

407
00:28:52,397 --> 00:28:56,332
- IS YOUR NOSE WHISTLING?
- I HAVE A DEVIATED SEPTUM.

408
00:28:57,969 --> 00:29:00,470
YOU KNOW, MR. PARKER
COULDN'T HAVE BEEN
THE NEXT OF KIN...

409
00:29:00,539 --> 00:29:03,006
TO HAVE YOU COMMITTED
IN THAT HOSPITAL
ON THAT SUICIDE WATCH.

410
00:29:03,075 --> 00:29:06,843
<i> THE DATES DON'T SQUARE.</i>
<i> MUTUMBO HAD ALREADY</i>
<i> SIPHONED AWAY MR. PARKER.</i>

411
00:29:06,912 --> 00:29:10,513
<i> SO, THE NEXT OF KIN</i>
<i> WOULD HAD TO HAVE BEEN--</i>

412
00:29:10,582 --> 00:29:14,317
LYLE.
LYLE TRAPPED ME THERE.

413
00:29:19,558 --> 00:29:21,658
DADDY?

414
00:29:21,727 --> 00:29:23,660
DADDY!

415
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:42,079
<i>I'M SORRY I CAN'T BE THERE</i>
<i>TO TALK TO YOU FACE-TO-FACE,</i>
<i>BUT, UH, PLANS CHANGE, HUH?</i>

416
00:29:42,147 --> 00:29:46,316
AFTER ALL,
IT IS THE CENTRE, RIGHT?

417
00:29:46,384 --> 00:29:50,520
NOW, I DON'T HAVE
A WHOLE HELL OF A LOT OF TIME,
SO PAY ATTENTION.

418
00:29:51,757 --> 00:29:54,224
THE WORLD IS CHANGING.

419
00:29:54,293 --> 00:29:57,227
THE CENTRE IS CHANGING.
I AM CHANGING.

420
00:29:57,296 --> 00:30:01,431
AND YOU?
YOU HAVE TO RIDE ALL THIS
CRAZY STUFF OUT, SEE?

421
00:30:01,500 --> 00:30:04,401
JUST, UH, RIDE HER OUT.
DON'T TRY TO FIND US.

422
00:30:04,470 --> 00:30:08,438
AND ABOVE ALL ELSE, ANGEL,
WATCH OUT FOR YOURSELF.

423
00:30:08,507 --> 00:30:11,875
DON'T FORGET--
"A FAMILY IS A TYRANNY"--

424
00:30:11,943 --> 00:30:13,876
"RULED OVER
BY ITS WEAKEST MEMBER."

425
00:30:13,945 --> 00:30:16,679
THANK GOD YOU'RE SAFE.
YOU HAD ME WORRIED.

426
00:30:16,748 --> 00:30:20,450
ABOUT WHAT?
THAT SUICIDAL SIS MIGHT PLAY
A LITTLE GAME OF RAZOR ROULETTE?

427
00:30:20,518 --> 00:30:22,785
THE SUICIDE WATCH WAS
FOR YOUR OWN PROTECTION.

428
00:30:22,854 --> 00:30:25,521
OH.
NOT PERFECT, BUT IT WAS
ALL I COULD THINK OF.

429
00:30:25,590 --> 00:30:28,892
THE MORE THE OTHERS THOUGHT
YOU WERE A NONFACTOR,
THE SAFER YOU'D BE.

430
00:30:28,961 --> 00:30:31,662
OTHERS?
THE SAME ONES
THAT GOT TO RAINES,

431
00:30:31,730 --> 00:30:33,730
THAT PUT THE SCARE
INTO OUR FATHER.

432
00:30:33,799 --> 00:30:36,265
WHICH CONVENIENTLY
PUT YOU IN CHARGE.

433
00:30:36,334 --> 00:30:39,268
MUTUMBO SNAPS, I JUMP.
GUILTY.

434
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:44,340
YOU AND YOUR TEAM--
I KNOW ALL ABOUT
YOUR COVERT DIVISION.

435
00:30:44,409 --> 00:30:47,477
MR. WHITE. SILENCE.

436
00:30:47,545 --> 00:30:49,612
GOOD, BECAUSE I
NEED YOUR HELP.

437
00:30:49,681 --> 00:30:53,016
LOOK, I'M BEING
STRAIGHT HERE.

438
00:30:53,085 --> 00:30:55,552
SILENCE IS
A LEVEL "A" CONTRACT.

439
00:30:55,620 --> 00:30:58,888
THE LAST THING I NEEDED
WAS FOR JAROD TO ESCAPE
AND MAKE THIS HIS CAUSE.

440
00:30:58,957 --> 00:31:00,757
CAREFUL.
YOU'RE SWEATING.

441
00:31:00,826 --> 00:31:03,893
WELL, WITH JAROD HOVERING,
I'D BE STUPID NOT TO.

442
00:31:03,962 --> 00:31:07,630
YOU BOTCH A LEVEL "A,"
AND YOU'LL NEED MY PRAYERS,
NOT MY HELP.

443
00:31:08,634 --> 00:31:10,767
I NEED MY SISTER.

444
00:31:10,835 --> 00:31:12,835
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN
A SURVIVOR, PARKER,

445
00:31:12,904 --> 00:31:15,905
BUT IN THE PAST YEAR SINCE
I FOUND MY FATHER AND YOU,

446
00:31:15,974 --> 00:31:20,010
I-- I'VE REALIZED IT'S NOT
JUST ME AGAINST THE WORLD.

447
00:31:20,078 --> 00:31:22,378
I HEAR THE WORLD'S
CHANGING.

448
00:31:22,447 --> 00:31:25,148
ONE LOOK INTO DAD'S EYES
CONFIRMS IT.

449
00:31:25,216 --> 00:31:28,518
<i> DESPITE THAT, THE CENTRE'S</i>
<i> ALWAYS BEEN ABOUT PARKERS.</i>

450
00:31:28,586 --> 00:31:31,655
AND LIKE IT OR NOT,
YOU AND I ARE IT.

451
00:31:31,723 --> 00:31:34,524
LET'S FIGHT FOR IT,
FOR US--

452
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:39,095
FOR HIM.

453
00:32:15,634 --> 00:32:18,401
[ Chiming ]

454
00:32:29,581 --> 00:32:31,414
<i>TIMSON.</i>

455
00:32:37,422 --> 00:32:40,157
<i> TIMSON!</i>

456
00:32:46,765 --> 00:32:48,698
[ Grunts ]
WHERE IS SHE?
WHERE'S CLARE NOW?

457
00:32:48,767 --> 00:32:52,068
JAROD! GONE. SHE'S
BEEN TAKEN OUT TO GO MEET
HER HUSBAND AND DAUGHTER.

458
00:32:52,137 --> 00:32:54,871
YOU WEREN'T TOLD ABOUT
THE SCHEDULE CHANGE?
NO, I WASN'T.

459
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:57,474
OUT OF THE BLUE,
THE TRANSFER ORDERS
WERE MOVED UP TO NOON.

460
00:32:57,542 --> 00:32:59,543
TIMSON.
YEAH.
THEY WERE HIS ORDERS.

461
00:32:59,611 --> 00:33:02,345
WHEN I ASKED FOR DETAILS,
HE SAID IT WAS
"NEED TO KNOW ONLY."

462
00:33:02,414 --> 00:33:05,414
GUESS TIMSON DOESN'T THINK
YOU AND I NEED TO.

463
00:33:12,324 --> 00:33:14,825
GLAD TO SEE YOU'VE DECIDED
TO TAKE UP THE FIGHT.

464
00:33:14,893 --> 00:33:18,695
I DIDN'T COME TO HELP YOU.
I CAME TO RECAPTURE JAROD.

465
00:34:22,894 --> 00:34:24,994
[ Beeping ]

466
00:34:27,565 --> 00:34:29,566
IT WON'T BE LONG NOW,
MRS. NASH.
THANK YOU.

467
00:34:29,634 --> 00:34:31,467
<i> [ Man On Radio ]</i>
<i> AGENT BLAINE.</i>

468
00:34:31,536 --> 00:34:33,803
- WE'RE IN POSITION.
-<i> ROGER THAT.</i>

469
00:34:33,872 --> 00:34:37,773
- SIR, "B" TEAM HAS MR. NASH AND
THEIR LITTLE GIRL IN POSITION.
- VERY GOOD.

470
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:43,046
<i> [ Door Opens ]</i>

471
00:34:45,183 --> 00:34:49,019
WELL, THIS IS AN HONOR.

472
00:34:49,087 --> 00:34:51,621
MURDERERS HAVE NO HONOR.

473
00:34:51,689 --> 00:34:54,924
NO, NO, NO.
MEETING YOU.

474
00:34:54,993 --> 00:34:57,027
I MEAN, MY GOD,
YOU'RE JAROD.

475
00:34:58,463 --> 00:35:02,031
<i>DIDN'T HAVE MUCH CHANCE</i>
<i>TO TALK ON THE PLANE.</i>

476
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:04,667
BY THE WAY, I OWE YOU
FOR SOME GREAT, GREAT FLYING.

477
00:35:04,736 --> 00:35:07,537
<i>THOUGHT I WAS TOAST.</i>
WHERE'S THE BOMB?

478
00:35:07,606 --> 00:35:10,807
YOU KNOW WHERE THE BOMB IS,
OTHERWISE YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE.

479
00:35:10,876 --> 00:35:13,210
<i>NOW, THAT SAID,</i>
<i>I'M LEAVING.</i>

480
00:35:13,278 --> 00:35:16,512
- I DON'T LIVE,
I DON'T GET PAID.
- YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

481
00:35:16,581 --> 00:35:19,849
WAS IT GOOD
SEEING YOUR DAD AGAIN?

482
00:35:19,918 --> 00:35:23,085
I MEAN,
YOU JUST BEAT ME TO HIM.

483
00:35:23,154 --> 00:35:25,221
BUT, HEY, HE'S NOW
OUT THERE AGAIN,

484
00:35:25,290 --> 00:35:28,391
<i>AND IT KIND OF</i>
<i>KEEPS ME IN BUSINESS,</i>
<i>YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?</i>

485
00:35:28,459 --> 00:35:30,126
BUSINESS?

486
00:35:30,195 --> 00:35:32,862
I'M A FINDER.
MISSING FAMILIES
ARE KIND OF MY NICHE.

487
00:35:32,931 --> 00:35:35,565
AND YOURS IS
A FULL-TIME JOB, BROTHER.

488
00:35:37,168 --> 00:35:39,702
WHAT ARE YOU GETTING AT?

489
00:35:39,771 --> 00:35:42,538
WELL, JUST THAT
OCCASIONALLY MR. LYLE...

490
00:35:42,607 --> 00:35:47,143
<i>WILL, UH, PAY ME</i>
<i>FOR SPECIAL PROJECTS.</i>

491
00:35:50,982 --> 00:35:53,783
<i>TAKE YOUR SISTER, EMILY,</i>
<i>FOR EXAMPLE.</i>

492
00:35:53,852 --> 00:35:55,852
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT MY SISTER?

493
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:59,322
THAT SHE ADORES YELLOW TULIPS,
SHE HATES CRUELTY TO ANIMALS,

494
00:35:59,391 --> 00:36:02,125
SHE'S SMART, SHE'S FUNNY,

495
00:36:02,193 --> 00:36:05,361
<i>SHE'S TORTURED</i>
<i>BY THE TRAGEDIES</i>
<i>OF HER FAMILY...</i>

496
00:36:05,430 --> 00:36:09,432
<i>AND THAT SHE HAS THE CUTEST</i>
<i>LITTLE TATTOO JUST ABOVE HER--</i>

497
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:12,369
UH-UH-UH!
HER LAST KNOWN ADDRESS
IS IN HERE.

498
00:36:12,437 --> 00:36:15,771
<i>THERE MIGHT EVEN BE SOME TIDBITS</i>
<i>ABOUT DEAR OLD MOM TOO.</i>

499
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:17,841
<i>SHAME TO SEE IT ALL GO POOF.</i>

500
00:36:17,909 --> 00:36:20,743
THERE MAY BE TIME FOR YOU
TO SAVE THAT FAMILY UPSTAIRS,

501
00:36:20,812 --> 00:36:23,813
MAYBE EVEN TIME FOR YOU
TO SAVE THIS FAMILY IN HERE.

502
00:36:23,882 --> 00:36:27,283
BUT YOU DO NOT GET ME
IN THE PACKAGE.

503
00:36:27,352 --> 00:36:29,385
<i>I'LL SEE YOU</i>
<i>ON DOWN THE ROAD.</i>

504
00:36:29,453 --> 00:36:31,554
<i> NO. NO!</i>

505
00:36:31,623 --> 00:36:33,556
[ Grunts ]

506
00:36:40,999 --> 00:36:44,466
<i> WE'LL HAVE A BETTER CHANCE</i>
<i> OF CATCHING JAROD</i>
<i> IF WE SPLIT UP.</i>

507
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:47,404
YOU THREE TAKE THE INTERIOR,
AND I'LL COVER OUTSIDE.

508
00:36:47,472 --> 00:36:49,772
FINE.

509
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:05,321
<i>CAN I SEE MY HUSBAND</i>
<i>AND DAUGHTER NOW?</i>

510
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:08,992
SOON. VERY SOON, MA'AM.
VERY SOON, MA'AM.

511
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:12,728
[ Rings ]
OH, EXCUSE ME.
THIS IS TIMSON.

512
00:37:12,797 --> 00:37:14,764
<i>YES, SIR.</i>
<i>ABSOLUTELY, SIR.</i>

513
00:37:14,833 --> 00:37:17,567
IF I'M NOT BACK IN,
UH, FIVE MINUTES,

514
00:37:17,636 --> 00:37:19,902
GO AHEAD AND BRING IN
NASH AND THE GIRL.

515
00:37:19,971 --> 00:37:21,904
- IT WON'T BE LONG NOW, MA'AM.
- THANKS.

516
00:37:21,973 --> 00:37:25,074
- SURE.
- OH, THERE YOU ARE.

517
00:37:25,143 --> 00:37:27,076
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

518
00:37:27,145 --> 00:37:30,446
I JUST CAME FROM
INSPECTOR WOCHECK'S OFFICE.

519
00:37:30,515 --> 00:37:33,249
HE SUSPECTS
THERE'S A CONTRACT OUT
ON MRS. NASH'S LIFE,

520
00:37:33,318 --> 00:37:35,819
AND THEY THINK THE HITTER
MIGHT BE WITHIN THE D.O.E.

521
00:37:35,887 --> 00:37:38,254
AH. UH, BLAINE,
YOU AND JAROD HERE
KEEP WATCH.

522
00:37:38,322 --> 00:37:40,823
<i> I'M GOING OUT</i>
<i> TO THE MOBILE UNIT</i>
<i> TO CONTACT THE INSPECTOR.</i>

523
00:37:40,892 --> 00:37:43,059
I CAN SAVE YOU
THAT TRIP, SIR.
NO, I GOTTA GO.

524
00:37:43,127 --> 00:37:46,262
INSPECTOR WOCHECK IS GONNA
CALL ME ON THIS CELL PHONE
AT 12:00 SHARP.

525
00:37:46,331 --> 00:37:50,466
THAT'S ONLY A FEW MINUTES AWAY.
I HAVE TO REVIEW THE PLACEMENT
OF MY AGENT PERIMETERS.

526
00:37:50,535 --> 00:37:52,768
-<i> YOU CAN USE MY WALKIE, SIR.</i>
- I DON'T WANT TO USE
YOUR DAMN WALKIE!

527
00:37:52,837 --> 00:37:54,971
<i> SPEAK WHEN YOU'RE</i>
<i> SPOKEN TO, AGENT.</i>
<i> EXCUSE ME.</i>

528
00:37:55,040 --> 00:37:57,006
IS THERE SOMETHING
THE MATTER?

529
00:37:57,075 --> 00:37:59,842
- NO.
- YOU SEEM LIKE YOU'RE IN
A HURRY TO GET SOMEWHERE.

530
00:37:59,911 --> 00:38:02,612
- WHAT THE HELL'S WRONG
WITH THIS THING?
- NOTHING.

531
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:05,615
<i> IT'S JUST, UH--</i>
<i> WELL, IT'S, UH--</i>
<i> IT'S LOCKED.</i>

532
00:38:05,683 --> 00:38:08,818
- OPEN IT.
- WHAT'S THE RUSH?

533
00:38:08,886 --> 00:38:11,487
OPEN THE DAMN DOOR! NOW!

534
00:38:11,556 --> 00:38:14,457
I-I DON'T UNDERSTAND. I--
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

535
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:20,196
THE PROBLEM IS,
IF YOU DON'T OPEN THE DOOR,
WE'RE GONNA BLOW UP, YOU IDIOT!

536
00:38:20,265 --> 00:38:26,035
- OH, MY GOD.
- OH, YOU MEAN THIS THING
I FOUND IS A BOMB?

537
00:38:26,104 --> 00:38:28,470
-<i> [ Beeping ]</i>
- DO SOMETHING!

538
00:38:28,539 --> 00:38:31,707
- KABOOM!
- [ Screams ]

539
00:38:31,776 --> 00:38:35,578
I FIND IT INTERESTING
THAT YOU KNEW THERE WAS
A BOMB IN THE BUILDING,

540
00:38:35,646 --> 00:38:37,714
BUT YOU DIDN'T BOTHER
TO TELL ANYBODY.

541
00:38:37,782 --> 00:38:41,017
<i> YOU WERE GOING TO ALLOW</i>
<i> AN INNOCENT FAMILY TO DIE--</i>

542
00:38:41,086 --> 00:38:43,919
AND YOUR OWN MEN--
IN AN EXPLOSION.

543
00:38:43,989 --> 00:38:46,356
AND FOR WHAT?

544
00:38:46,424 --> 00:38:50,427
AGENT BLAINE?
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.

545
00:38:50,495 --> 00:38:52,662
IT WOULD BE
MY PLEASURE, JAROD.

546
00:39:03,875 --> 00:39:06,375
I THINK YOU'RE HERE
TO SEE SOME SPECIAL PEOPLE.

547
00:39:06,444 --> 00:39:08,745
YEAH.

548
00:39:08,813 --> 00:39:10,813
<i> [ Gasps ]</i>
<i> OH, MY BABY!</i>

549
00:39:10,882 --> 00:39:13,115
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> THERE'S A BROWN SEDAN</i>
<i> IN THE PARKING LOT.</i>

550
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:16,252
HERE'S ALL THE INFORMATION
YOU NEED TO START YOUR NEW LIFE.

551
00:39:16,321 --> 00:39:19,455
YOU'LL BE SAFE.
I PROMISE YOU.

552
00:39:19,524 --> 00:39:23,025
BUT-- BUT WHO ARE YOU?
NO, IT'S ALL RIGHT.
WE CAN TRUST HIM.

553
00:39:24,862 --> 00:39:29,565
OH, JAROD, I HOPE THAT ONE DAY
YOU AND YOUR FAMILY CAN FEEL
THIS MOMENT TOO.

554
00:39:29,634 --> 00:39:32,135
[ Kisses,
Chuckles ]

555
00:39:33,304 --> 00:39:35,638
GOOD LUCK.
BYE.

556
00:40:03,568 --> 00:40:06,569
- PARKER.
- OUR WORK'S DONE HERE.

557
00:40:06,637 --> 00:40:08,904
WHAT, HE GOT AWAY? HOW?

558
00:40:10,175 --> 00:40:12,675
YOU SHOULDN'T
UNDERESTIMATE JAROD.
MM-MMM.

559
00:40:12,743 --> 00:40:16,712
AND YOU SHOULD NEVER
UNDERESTIMATE ME.

560
00:40:16,781 --> 00:40:20,283
AND THE NEXT TIME THAT
YOU SEND ME INTO A BUILDING
THAT'S GONNA EXPLODE,

561
00:40:20,351 --> 00:40:22,351
IT HAD BETTER BLOW,

562
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:24,987
BECAUSE IF IT DOESN'T,
IT'S GONNA BE
YOUR GRAY MATTER...

563
00:40:25,056 --> 00:40:28,458
THEY'LL BE MOPPING UP
WITH A TOOTHBRUSH.

564
00:40:28,526 --> 00:40:30,693
BY THE WAY,
JAROD LEFT YOU SOMETHING.

565
00:40:39,837 --> 00:40:42,071
<i>[ Mr. Parker</i>
<i>  On Answering Machine ]</i>
<i>OH, MY ANGEL.</i>

566
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:45,841
GOD, I'M SORRY I MISSED YOU.
I WANTED TO HEAR YOUR VOICE.
NEEDED TO.

567
00:40:45,910 --> 00:40:48,411
<i>NOW, IF YOU DON'T HEAR FROM ME,</i>
<i>DON'T YOU WORRY.</i>

568
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:51,547
<i> BRIGITTE AND I ARE SAFE.</i>
<i> AT LEAST I THINK I AM.</i>

569
00:40:51,616 --> 00:40:54,850
<i> IT'S ALWAYS WHEN YOU THINK</i>
<i> YOU ARE, THAT'S WHEN YOU'RE</i>
<i> THE MOST VULNERABLE.</i>

570
00:40:54,919 --> 00:40:57,153
<i> NOW, DON'T YOU MAKE</i>
<i> THE SAME MISTAKE I DID.</i>

571
00:40:57,221 --> 00:41:00,990
<i>NOW, DON'T EXPOSE</i>
<i>THE SOFT UNDERBELLY.</i>
<i>THEY TARGET THAT.</i>

572
00:41:01,059 --> 00:41:05,895
<i> NO, NO, NO. YOU CATCH JAROD</i>
<i> AND NEVER, EVER LET HIM GO.</i>

573
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:09,632
<i> DAMN IT! HE'S THE KEY.</i>
<i> HE'S THE ONLY KEY.</i>
<i> ALWAYS HAS BEEN.</i>

574
00:41:09,701 --> 00:41:12,868
<i>AND THERE'S ONE LAST THING--</i>
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

575
00:41:12,937 --> 00:41:16,038
<i> 'CAUSE I KNOW YOU'RE TOUGH,</i>
<i> I'M NOT WORRIED.</i>

576
00:41:16,107 --> 00:41:18,107
<i> YOU WATCH YOUR BACK</i>
<i> AT THE CENTRE.</i>

577
00:41:18,176 --> 00:41:20,176
<i> NOBODY'S WHAT</i>
<i> THEY SEEM TO BE.</i>

578
00:41:20,245 --> 00:41:25,548
<i>THERE'S NO SOUL IN THAT PLACE--</i>
<i>NOT ONE-- THAT YOU CAN TRUST,</i>

579
00:41:25,617 --> 00:41:28,784
<i> WITH THE POSSIBLE EXCEPTION</i>
<i> OF YOUR BROTHER.</i>

580
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:37,994
[ Chattering ]

581
00:41:44,001 --> 00:41:47,403
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

582
00:41:47,472 --> 00:41:51,440
MY NAME IS JAROD.
HAVE YOU SEEN THIS WOMAN?

583
00:41:51,509 --> 00:41:56,179
LIKE I SAID,
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?
I'M HER BROTHER.

584
00:41:56,247 --> 00:42:00,216
<i> DAMN. SHE'S GONNA</i>
<i> BE SORRY SHE MISSED YOU,</i>
<i> BUT SHE JUST LEFT TODAY.</i>

585
00:42:00,285 --> 00:42:05,955
SHE WOULDN'T SAY WHERE.
SORT OF LIKE SHE THOUGHT SOMEONE
WAS FOLLOWIN' HER. SWEET GIRL.

586
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:08,357
WAS SHE ALONE?
YEAH, BUT SHE
DIDN'T WANT TO BE.

587
00:42:08,426 --> 00:42:11,527
SHE WAS SEARCHIN' FOR
HER FAMILY. SAID SHE WAS
DETERMINED TO FIND THEM.

588
00:42:11,595 --> 00:42:13,863
LIKE I SAID,

589
00:42:13,931 --> 00:42:16,598
SHE'D BE SORRY
IF SHE KNEW SHE MISSED YOU.

590
00:42:16,667 --> 00:42:18,600
YEAH.

591
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:26,442
<i>[ Electricity Crackling ]</i>

592
00:42:30,348 --> 00:42:32,348
[ Rings ]

593
00:42:34,118 --> 00:42:36,052
WHAT?

594
00:42:36,121 --> 00:42:38,621
AT LEAST WE PUT
ONE FAMILY BACK TOGETHER.

595
00:42:38,689 --> 00:42:41,790
- WHILE MINE
GOT RIPPED APART AGAIN.
- I KNOW THE FEELING.

596
00:42:41,860 --> 00:42:45,861
YOU KNOW, JAROD,
MAYBE LYLE'S RIGHT.
MAYBE THE WORLD IS CHANGING.

597
00:42:45,930 --> 00:42:48,430
IT DOESN'T SEEM TO MATTER
HOW MUCH IT CHANGES.

598
00:42:48,499 --> 00:42:51,133
IT'S STILL THE SAME FOR US.

599
00:42:52,704 --> 00:42:54,704
WE'RE STILL ALONE IN IT.

